text: thumb Gita Nabavi (born 14 February 1982) is a Swedish politician. On 24 February 2018, she was elected leader of the Feminist Initiative, along with its founder Gudrun Schyman. In February 2020, Nabavi resigned from her post, stating that she wanted to spend more time with her children. ==References== Category:1982 births Category:Living people Category:Swedish feminists Category:Feminist Initiative (Sweden) politicians Category:Swedish people of Iranian descent
